<section id="usage">
	<div class="display-wrap separator">
		<div class="grid g-cols">
			<div class="g-col-12">
				<h5>Usage</h5>
				<p class="body l--fs-7 lh-6 pt-4 pb-4"><strong>Lead-in title, heading, body content and CTA</strong></p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="grid g-cols pt-4">
			<div class="g-col-12">
				<div class="container bordered padding-large mb-4">
					<%= image_tag "type-example1", width: "100%" %>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="grid g-cols pt-2 gap-l">
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class=""><strong>1 - Lead-in Title</strong></p>
				Use a lead-in title to introduce and describe the topic of your accompanying copy. It always remains the same style.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class=""><strong>2 - Main Heading</strong></p>
				Headings can be used on their own but should be descriptive and powerful in their overall meaning. Should always be Poppins Bold.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class=""><strong>3 - Body Copy</strong></p>
				Body copy allows you to describe your topic from your heading or lead-in title. Default size is 14px.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class=""><strong>4 - CTA</strong></p>
				When speaking of a topic, always consider accompanying your copy with a CTA so visitors can learn more about your topic.
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="grid g-cols pt-8">
			<div class="g-col-12">
				<p class="body l--fs-7 lh-6 pt-4 pb-4"><strong>Small titles with body and CTA</strong></p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="grid g-cols pt-4">
			<div class="g-col-12">
				<div class="container bordered padding-large mb-5">
					<%= image_tag "type-example2", width: "100%" %>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="grid g-cols gap-m pt-6">
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class="text_size-3"><strong>1 - Title</strong></p>
				Titles, much like their big sibling <a href="#headings">headings</a> are used to describe the context of the following paragraph copy.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class="text_size-3"><strong>2 - Body Copy</strong></p>
				The size of body copy should be smaller than the title. In this example the title is 18px and body is 16px.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				<p class="text_size-3"><strong>3 - CTA</strong></p>
				The CTA always allows the reader to read more on the topic just discussed. Use it as much as possible when discussing topics.
			</div>
			<div class="l--g-col-3 m--g-col-6 g-col-12">
				&nbsp;
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

